      "rawMarkdown": "# 32. Advocate\n\n**Pronunciation:** AD-vuh-kayt / AD-vuh-kit\n**Part of speech:** Verb / Noun\n**Core meaning:** To support or argue in favor of something; a supporter.\n**Bangla meaning:** সমর্থন করা, পক্ষ নেওয়া, প্রবক্তা\n\n**Root story / etymology:** From Latin *advocare*: *ad-* = toward + *vocare* = to call. Originally, an advocate was someone “called to help” in court.\n\n**Simple explanation:** To advocate a policy, reform, idea, or right means to support it openly with reasons.\n\n**Memory hook:** **Advocate = a voice called to support.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** champion, endorse, support, promote, espouse\n**Basic synonyms:** back, favor, recommend, argue for\n**Antonyms:** oppose, reject, criticize, denounce\n**Common usage:** advocate reform, advocate change, advocate for rights, environmental advocate\n**Confusing word:** **Advocate ≠ Avocado.** Advocate = সমর্থক; avocado = fruit.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. She advocates equal education for all children.\n2. The doctor advocated regular exercise.\n3. He is an advocate for clean energy.\n4. Many economists advocate investment in infrastructure.\n5. The report advocates stricter safety standards.\n6. The professor advocated a more evidence-based approach.\n7. Environmental groups advocate reducing plastic waste.\n8. In public policy, researchers often advocate reforms after studying long-term social costs.\n9. The article advocates renewable energy not as an idealistic dream, but as an economically feasible transition.\n10. The committee advocated transparency because secrecy had weakened public trust.\n\n### GRE synonym examples — 15\n\n1. She **championed** the rights of rural students.\n2. The senator **championed** healthcare reform.\n3. The committee **endorsed** the proposal after reviewing the evidence.\n4. Several experts **endorsed** the new safety guideline.\n5. The paper **supports** stronger environmental regulation.\n6. Data **support** the need for early intervention.\n7. The organization **promotes** literacy among disadvantaged children.\n8. The campaign **promotes** vaccination awareness.\n9. He **espoused** democratic values throughout his career.\n10. The philosopher **espoused** nonviolence.\n11. The university **backed** the student research initiative.\n12. The report **recommends** stricter emission limits.\n13. The lawyer **argued for** a fairer trial process.\n14. The activist **favored** policies that protected workers.\n15. The editorial **endorsed** the reform but criticized its weak implementation.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Advocate = support with a voice = সমর্থন করা**\n\n---",
