      "rawMarkdown": "# 34. Alacrity\n\n**Pronunciation:** uh-LAK-ruh-tee\n**Part of speech:** Noun\n**Core meaning:** Cheerful eagerness and quick willingness to do something.\n**Bangla meaning:** সানন্দ তৎপরতা, আগ্রহী দ্রুততা, উৎসাহের সঙ্গে প্রস্তুতি\n\n**Root story / etymology:** From Latin *alacer*, meaning “lively, cheerful, eager.” The word carries both speed and willingness.\n\n**Simple explanation:** Alacrity is not just speed. It means doing something quickly and gladly.\n\n**Memory hook:** **Alacrity = eager + quick action.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** eagerness, promptness, enthusiasm, readiness, briskness\n**Basic synonyms:** willingness, speed, quickness, energy\n**Antonyms:** reluctance, hesitation, unwillingness, delay\n**Common usage:** respond with alacrity, accept with alacrity, move with alacrity\n**Confusing word:** **Alacrity ≠ Electricity.** Alacrity means eager quickness, not power/current.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. She accepted the invitation with alacrity.\n2. The volunteers worked with alacrity.\n3. He answered the teacher’s question with alacrity.\n4. The rescue team responded with alacrity after the warning.\n5. The students joined the research project with unexpected alacrity.\n6. The assistant completed the urgent task with alacrity.\n7. Investors welcomed the new policy with alacrity.\n8. In disaster management, agencies must respond with alacrity when early warnings indicate danger.\n9. In laboratory work, researchers handled the equipment with alacrity but not carelessness.\n10. The committee approved the emergency funding with alacrity because delay would have worsened the crisis.\n\n### GRE synonym examples — 15\n\n1. The interns showed great **eagerness** to learn.\n2. The nurse acted with remarkable **promptness**.\n3. The students joined the debate with **enthusiasm**.\n4. The team’s **readiness** impressed the supervisor.\n5. His **briskness** made the meeting efficient.\n6. The firefighters responded with **speed**.\n7. She approached the difficult assignment with **willingness**.\n8. The committee moved with unusual **quickness**.\n9. The child’s **enthusiasm** made the class lively.\n10. The officer’s **promptness** prevented further damage.\n11. Their **readiness** to help reduced the pressure on the hospital.\n12. The employees accepted overtime with surprising **eagerness**.\n13. The lab team showed **brisk efficiency** during the trial.\n14. The volunteers’ **willingness** made the campaign successful.\n15. His **energetic response** showed that he was not merely obedient but genuinely eager.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Alacrity = cheerful quickness = সানন্দ তৎপরতা**\n\n---",
