      "rawMarkdown": "# 37. Amenable\n\n**Pronunciation:** uh-MEE-nuh-bəl\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Willing to accept advice, suggestion, control, or change.\n**Bangla meaning:** রাজি, অনুকূল, পরামর্শ গ্রহণে প্রস্তুত, মান্যকারী\n\n**Root story / etymology:** Historically connected to the idea of being “answerable” or “liable to be brought to account.” Modern meaning: responsive or willing to cooperate.\n\n**Simple explanation:** If someone is amenable, they are not stubborn. They can listen, adjust, and cooperate.\n\n**Memory hook:** **Amenable = able to say “amen” to a reasonable idea.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** compliant, receptive, cooperative, tractable, acquiescent\n**Basic synonyms:** willing, open, flexible, agreeable\n**Antonyms:** stubborn, resistant, uncooperative, obstinate\n**Common usage:** amenable to suggestion, amenable to change, amenable student, amenable solution\n**Confusing word:** **Amenable ≠ Amiable.** Amenable = willing to cooperate; amiable = friendly.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. He is amenable to advice.\n2. The manager was amenable to our proposal.\n3. She is usually amenable to feedback.\n4. The design is amenable to modification.\n5. The patient was amenable to treatment.\n6. The committee became more amenable after seeing the data.\n7. A good research method should be amenable to testing and replication.\n8. In engineering design, modular systems are amenable to repair and upgrade.\n9. The professor was not hostile; she was amenable to changing the deadline if students had valid reasons.\n10. The policy is amenable to gradual reform, but sudden changes may create resistance.\n\n### GRE synonym examples — 15\n\n1. The employee was **compliant** with safety rules.\n2. The patient was **compliant** with the treatment plan.\n3. The board was **receptive** to new evidence.\n4. Students were **receptive** to constructive criticism.\n5. The team remained **cooperative** during the investigation.\n6. A **cooperative** attitude helped resolve the conflict.\n7. The child was unusually **tractable** after the teacher explained the rules.\n8. The model is **tractable** enough for numerical analysis.\n9. The assistant was **acquiescent**, accepting the decision without protest.\n10. The committee was **open** to revision.\n11. The company became **flexible** after customer complaints.\n12. The proposal was **agreeable** to most stakeholders.\n13. The system is **adaptable** to different climates.\n14. The negotiators were **willing** to compromise.\n15. The new algorithm is **receptive** to parameter tuning, making it useful for experimental studies.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Amenable = willing to cooperate/change = রাজি ও অনুকূল**\n\n---",
