      "rawMarkdown": "# 38. Anachronistic\n\n**Pronunciation:** uh-nak-ruh-NIS-tik\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Belonging to the wrong time period; outdated.\n**Bangla meaning:** কালবিরোধী, সময়ের সঙ্গে অসামঞ্জস্যপূর্ণ, সেকেলে\n\n**Root story / etymology:** From Greek *ana-* = back/against + *chronos* = time. Anachronistic means placed against the correct time.\n\n**Simple explanation:** Something anachronistic seems old-fashioned or historically out of place.\n\n**Memory hook:** **Chronos = time; anachronistic = wrong time.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** outdated, antiquated, archaic, obsolete, old-fashioned\n**Basic synonyms:** old, outdated, behind the times, out of date\n**Antonyms:** modern, current, contemporary, up-to-date\n**Common usage:** anachronistic law, anachronistic custom, anachronistic belief, anachronistic technology\n**Confusing word:** **Anachronistic ≠ Anarchistic.** Anachronistic = out of time; anarchistic = against government/order.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. Using a typewriter today may seem anachronistic.\n2. The law feels anachronistic in the digital age.\n3. The movie showed a smartphone in ancient Rome; that was anachronistic.\n4. Some workplace rules are anachronistic and need revision.\n5. The policy is anachronistic because it was designed before the internet.\n6. The textbook’s view of gender roles is deeply anachronistic.\n7. The museum removed an anachronistic painting from the medieval display.\n8. In legal studies, anachronistic regulations often fail to address modern technological problems.\n9. In engineering education, ignoring simulation tools would be anachronistic in a data-driven era.\n10. The researcher argued that applying nineteenth-century assumptions to modern climate policy is anachronistic.\n\n### GRE synonym examples — 15\n\n1. The software is **outdated** and insecure.\n2. The law is **outdated** because it ignores online banking.\n3. The building has an **antiquated** heating system.\n4. The committee rejected the **antiquated** procedure.\n5. The manuscript used **archaic** language.\n6. The institution preserved several **archaic** customs.\n7. The machine became **obsolete** after automation improved.\n8. Some skills become **obsolete** when technology changes.\n9. The rule seemed **old-fashioned** to younger employees.\n10. His ideas about education were **behind the times**.\n11. The policy was no longer **current**.\n12. The device was **outmoded** by modern standards.\n13. The system was **dated**, though still functional.\n14. The curriculum looked **antiquated** because it ignored computational tools.\n15. The historian criticized the film for using **anachronistic** dialogue in a medieval setting.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Anachronistic = wrong time / outdated = কালবিরোধী**\n\n---",
