      "rawMarkdown": "# 43. Brazen\n\n**Pronunciation:** BRAY-zən\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Shamelessly bold; showing no embarrassment for bad behavior.\n**Bangla meaning:** নির্লজ্জভাবে সাহসী, বেহায়া, প্রকাশ্যে বেপরোয়া\n\n**Root story / etymology:** Originally related to brass. Brass is hard and bright; figuratively, brazen came to mean “bold-faced” and shameless.\n\n**Simple explanation:** Brazen describes bold behavior that should cause shame, but the person shows no shame.\n\n**Memory hook:** **Brazen = bold as brass, no shame.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** impudent, shameless, insolent, audacious, blatant\n**Basic synonyms:** bold, rude, open, disrespectful\n**Antonyms:** modest, shy, humble, discreet\n**Common usage:** brazen lie, brazen corruption, brazen attack, brazen disregard\n**Confusing word:** **Brazen ≠ Brave.** Brave = courageous; brazen = shamelessly bold.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. He told a brazen lie.\n2. The thief made a brazen escape.\n3. Her brazen disrespect shocked the class.\n4. The official denied the charge with brazen confidence.\n5. The company made a brazen claim without evidence.\n6. The student made a brazen attempt to cheat.\n7. The mayor’s brazen corruption angered voters.\n8. In political reporting, brazen violations of law often trigger public outrage.\n9. In cybersecurity, a brazen attack may involve hackers openly demanding ransom.\n10. The paper criticized the corporation’s brazen greenwashing, arguing that its environmental claims contradicted its actual emissions record.\n\n### GRE synonym examples — 15\n\n1. His **impudent** reply angered the teacher.\n2. The employee’s **impudent** tone was unacceptable.\n3. The politician made a **shameless** excuse.\n4. The company’s **shameless** exploitation drew criticism.\n5. The student’s **insolent** behavior shocked the examiner.\n6. The officer punished the soldier’s **insolent** remark.\n7. The thief made an **audacious** attempt to escape.\n8. The claim was **audacious** but unsupported.\n9. The advertisement contained a **blatant** lie.\n10. The report exposed **blatant** corruption.\n11. His **bold-faced** denial fooled no one.\n12. The manager’s **rude** dismissal upset the staff.\n13. The company showed **open** disregard for safety.\n14. The official’s **brazen** refusal to answer questions intensified suspicion.\n15. The court condemned the defendant’s **shameless** attempt to profit from public funds.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Brazen = shamelessly bold = নির্লজ্জ সাহসী**\n\n---",
