      "rawMarkdown": "# 50. Convoluted\n\n**Pronunciation:** KON-vuh-loo-tid\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Very complicated and difficult to follow.\n**Bangla meaning:** জটিল, প্যাঁচানো, বোঝা কঠিন\n\n**Root story / etymology:** From Latin *convolvere*: *con-* = together + *volvere* = to roll. Something convoluted is “rolled together” into confusing complexity.\n\n**Simple explanation:** A convoluted explanation, law, argument, or process is unnecessarily complex.\n\n**Memory hook:** **Convoluted = coiled and confusing.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** complicated, intricate, labyrinthine, tangled, elaborate\n**Basic synonyms:** complex, confusing, twisted, difficult\n**Antonyms:** simple, clear, straightforward, plain\n**Common usage:** convoluted argument, convoluted plot, convoluted law, convoluted explanation\n**Confusing word:** **Convoluted ≠ Convicted.** Convoluted = complicated; convicted = found guilty.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. The instructions were convoluted.\n2. The movie had a convoluted plot.\n3. His explanation was too convoluted to follow.\n4. The tax code is often criticized as convoluted.\n5. The report’s convoluted structure weakened its argument.\n6. The contract was so convoluted that even lawyers debated its meaning.\n7. The theory became convoluted after too many exceptions were added.\n8. In policy analysis, convoluted regulations often reduce compliance.\n9. In engineering documentation, convoluted diagrams can create safety risks.\n10. The article’s central claim was reasonable, but the author buried it under convoluted reasoning.\n\n### GRE synonym examples — 15\n\n1. The problem was more **complicated** than expected.\n2. The data produced a **complicated** pattern.\n3. The machine had an **intricate** control system.\n4. The novel’s **intricate** structure rewarded careful reading.\n5. The legal process was **labyrinthine**.\n6. The bureaucracy became **labyrinthine** after years of reform.\n7. The wires were **tangled** behind the machine.\n8. The argument became **tangled** with irrelevant details.\n9. The design was **elaborate** but inefficient.\n10. The explanation was **complex** without being clear.\n11. The route was **twisted** through narrow streets.\n12. The theory was **obscure** to beginners.\n13. The procedure was **cumbersome** and slow.\n14. The discussion became **confusing** because terms were not defined.\n15. The reviewer criticized the manuscript for its **convoluted** logic and unclear methodology.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Convoluted = complicated and hard to follow = জটিল**\n\n---",
