      "rawMarkdown": "# 53. Decorum\n\n**Pronunciation:** dih-KOR-um\n**Part of speech:** Noun\n**Core meaning:** Proper, polite, and socially acceptable behavior.\n**Bangla meaning:** শালীনতা, ভদ্রতা, যথাযথ আচরণ, সামাজিক নিয়মরীতি\n\n**Root story / etymology:** From Latin *decorus*, meaning “fitting, proper, becoming.” Decorum is behavior that fits the situation.\n\n**Simple explanation:** Decorum means knowing how to behave properly in formal or respectful settings.\n\n**Memory hook:** **Decorum = decent conduct in the room.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** propriety, etiquette, civility, dignity, protocol\n**Basic synonyms:** politeness, manners, respect, good behavior\n**Antonyms:** rudeness, impropriety, vulgarity, disorder\n**Common usage:** maintain decorum, courtroom decorum, public decorum, sense of decorum\n**Confusing word:** **Decorum ≠ Decoration.** Decorum = proper behavior; decoration = ornament.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. Students must maintain decorum in class.\n2. The judge demanded decorum in the courtroom.\n3. His behavior lacked decorum.\n4. The ceremony required formal decorum.\n5. The debate lost decorum when speakers began shouting.\n6. The professor reminded students of academic decorum.\n7. Public officials should act with decorum during national crises.\n8. In parliamentary systems, decorum helps prevent debate from becoming personal conflict.\n9. In professional meetings, decorum allows disagreement without disrespect.\n10. The report criticized the committee not for disagreement, but for abandoning decorum during discussion.\n\n### GRE synonym examples — 15\n\n1. The diplomat behaved with perfect **propriety**.\n2. The letter followed the rules of professional **propriety**.\n3. Good **etiquette** matters in formal interviews.\n4. The manual explained business **etiquette**.\n5. Public **civility** declined during the heated debate.\n6. The teacher encouraged **civility** among students.\n7. The president spoke with **dignity** after the tragedy.\n8. The ceremony required quiet **dignity**.\n9. The hospital followed strict safety **protocol**.\n10. Diplomatic **protocol** shaped the meeting.\n11. Her **manners** impressed the guests.\n12. The audience showed **respect** during the memorial.\n13. The discussion remained **polite** despite disagreement.\n14. The official maintained **composure** under criticism.\n15. The court warned that without **decorum**, legal proceedings would lose authority.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Decorum = proper respectful behavior = শালীনতা**\n\n---",
