      "rawMarkdown": "# 57. Desiccate\n\n**Pronunciation:** DES-ih-kayt\n**Part of speech:** Verb\n**Core meaning:** To dry out completely.\n**Bangla meaning:** শুকিয়ে ফেলা, সম্পূর্ণ শুষ্ক করা, পানি/আর্দ্রতা সরিয়ে দেওয়া\n\n**Root story / etymology:** From Latin *desiccare*: *de-* = thoroughly + *siccus* = dry. So desiccate means to make thoroughly dry.\n\n**Simple explanation:** To desiccate something means to remove moisture from it until it becomes dry.\n\n**Memory hook:** **Desiccate = dry like a desert.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** dehydrate, dry out, parch, shrivel, drain\n**Basic synonyms:** dry, remove moisture, wither, preserve by drying\n**Antonyms:** moisten, hydrate, soak, dampen\n**Common usage:** desiccate plants, desiccated fruit, desiccated soil, desiccated tissue\n**Confusing word:** **Desiccate ≠ Dedicate.** Desiccate = dry out; dedicate = devote.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. The sun desiccated the soil.\n2. The desert wind desiccated the plants.\n3. The fruit was desiccated for storage.\n4. Long droughts can desiccate farmland.\n5. The sample was desiccated before weighing.\n6. The leaves became desiccated after weeks without rain.\n7. The laboratory used heat to desiccate the specimen.\n8. In materials science, moisture-sensitive samples are desiccated before testing.\n9. In climate research, prolonged heat waves can desiccate entire agricultural regions.\n10. The study found that repeated drought cycles desiccated the wetland and reduced biodiversity.\n\n### GRE synonym examples — 15\n\n1. The machine **dehydrated** the fruit.\n2. Heat can **dehydrate** human tissue.\n3. The riverbed began to **dry out**.\n4. The sun **dried out** the clay.\n5. The drought **parched** the fields.\n6. The hot wind **parched** his lips.\n7. The leaves **shriveled** in the heat.\n8. The fruit **shriveled** after losing moisture.\n9. The process **drained** water from the sample.\n10. The soil became **arid** after months of drought.\n11. The plant **withered** without irrigation.\n12. The meat was **cured** through drying.\n13. The specimen was **preserved** by removing moisture.\n14. The air was so dry that it **dehydrated** exposed materials.\n15. The experiment required researchers to **desiccate** the sample before measuring its dry mass.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Desiccate = dry out completely = শুকিয়ে ফেলা**\n\n---",
