      "rawMarkdown": "# 60. Ingenuous\n\n**Pronunciation:** in-JEN-yoo-əs\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Innocent, sincere, and without deception.\n**Bangla meaning:** সরল, নিষ্পাপ, অকপট, ছলনাহীন\n\n**Root story / etymology:** From Latin *ingenuus*, meaning “free-born, noble, natural.” It developed the sense of open, honest, and innocent.\n\n**Simple explanation:** Ingenuous describes someone who is honest and innocent, sometimes because they are inexperienced.\n\n**Memory hook:** **Ingenuous = innocent and genuine.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** naive, innocent, artless, guileless, sincere\n**Basic synonyms:** simple, honest, open, trusting\n**Antonyms:** deceitful, cunning, crafty, sophisticated\n**Common usage:** ingenuous child, ingenuous smile, ingenuous honesty, ingenuous question\n**Confusing word:** **Ingenuous ≠ Ingenious.** Ingenuous = innocent/sincere; ingenious = clever/inventive.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. The child gave an ingenuous answer.\n2. Her ingenuous smile made everyone trust her.\n3. He was too ingenuous to suspect fraud.\n4. The student asked an ingenuous but important question.\n5. His ingenuous honesty impressed the interviewers.\n6. The narrator’s ingenuous perspective makes the novel emotionally powerful.\n7. The young researcher’s ingenuous trust in published data was later shaken.\n8. In literature, an ingenuous narrator may reveal truths unintentionally.\n9. In business, ingenuous clients can be exploited by dishonest sellers.\n10. The committee appreciated his ingenuous admission that he did not fully understand the technical issue.\n\n### GRE synonym examples — 15\n\n1. The **naive** traveler trusted everyone.\n2. The policy was criticized as **naive** because it ignored political realities.\n3. The child’s **innocent** question exposed the flaw.\n4. His **innocent** expression made the accusation seem unlikely.\n5. Her **artless** manner charmed the audience.\n6. The memoir’s **artless** style made it feel sincere.\n7. The witness seemed **guileless** and honest.\n8. His **guileless** trust made him vulnerable.\n9. She gave a **sincere** apology.\n10. The student’s **sincere** curiosity impressed the professor.\n11. His **open** manner made him approachable.\n12. The child was **trusting** by nature.\n13. Her response was **honest** rather than strategic.\n14. The young intern’s **simple** confidence was touching.\n15. The novel’s protagonist is **ingenuous**, not foolish: her innocence allows her to see hypocrisy clearly.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Ingenuous = innocent and sincere = সরল / নিষ্পাপ**\n\n---\n\n## Compact Summary Table — Words 46–60\n\n| No. | Word        | Core Meaning              | Bangla        | GRE Synonyms                 | Antonym      |\n| --: | ----------- | ------------------------- | ------------- | ---------------------------- | ------------ |\n|  46 | Castigate   | criticize severely        | তিরস্কার করা  | reprimand, rebuke, censure   | praise       |\n|  47 | Caustic     | burning; sharply critical | দাহক, তীক্ষ্ণ | corrosive, biting, scathing  | gentle       |\n|  48 | Construe    | interpret meaning         | ব্যাখ্যা করা  | interpret, infer, understand | misinterpret |\n|  49 | Contrite    | sincerely sorry           | অনুতপ্ত       | remorseful, repentant        | unrepentant  |\n|  50 | Convoluted  | very complicated          | জটিল          | intricate, labyrinthine      | simple       |\n|  51 | Covet       | strongly desire           | লোভ করা       | crave, yearn for, envy       | reject       |\n|  52 | Craven      | cowardly                  | কাপুরুষ       | pusillanimous, timid         | brave        |\n|  53 | Decorum     | proper behavior           | শালীনতা       | propriety, etiquette         | rudeness     |\n|  54 | Deft        | skillful and quick        | দক্ষ          | adept, dexterous, adroit     | clumsy       |\n|  55 | Demur       | object or hesitate        | আপত্তি করা    | object, dissent, balk        | agree        |\n|  56 | Derivative  | not original              | অনুকরণমূলক    | imitative, unoriginal        | original     |\n|  57 | Desiccate   | dry out fully             | শুকিয়ে ফেলা   | dehydrate, parch             | moisten      |\n|  58 | Diatribe    | bitter verbal attack      | তীব্র নিন্দা  | tirade, rant, invective      | praise       |\n|  59 | Incredulous | unbelieving               | অবিশ্বাসী     | skeptical, doubtful          | credulous    |\n|  60 | Ingenuous   | innocent and sincere      | সরল, নিষ্পাপ  | naive, guileless             | deceitful    |\n\n---",
